      • parseQuery

        public static void parseQuery(java.lang.String query,
                              java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> parameters)
                       throws java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException
        Gets url query string and parse into key-value data. parameters would be Map with String keys and String if key in url is used once List<String> if key in url is used multiple.

        Example Code: 

             
     Util.parseQuery(httpExchange.getRequestURI().getRawQuery(), params);
        Parameters:
        query - gets the query string
        parameters - parameters map to contain
        Throws:
        java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException - when it cannot be encoded
